Liverpool Striker Suarez Denies Racist Abuse Toward Evra: Soccer Roundup

-- B y   A l e x   D u f f
-- 
2011-10-17T09:07:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-17/liverpool-striker-suarez-denies-racist-abuse-toward-evra-soccer-roundup.html
The following is a roundup of soccer
stories from U.K. newspapers, with clickable links to the Web.  Suarez Denial  Liverpool’s  Luis Suarez  has denied repeatedly aiming racial
abuse at  Manchester United ’s Patrice Evra during a 1-1 Premier
League draw at the weekend,  the Guardian  reported.  Liverpool wants Evra to receive a ban should his
accusations prove groundless, the Guardian said.  Everton Chase  Everton and Blackburn are trailing Hoffenheim striker Vedad
Ibisevic, the  Daily Mirror  reported.  The Bosnian was set to sign for Blackburn in the offseason
before fitness doubts scuppered a deal, the Mirror said. He
returned from injury at the weekend.  United Teenager  Manchester United faces a tussle to keep 18-year-old French
midfielder Paul Pogba, the  Daily Mirror  said.  Pogba’s contract is running out two years after he joined
from  Le Havre , the Mirror said. He entered as a substitute in
United’s Carling Cup win against Leeds last month.  Van Persie Stays  Robin van Persie  says he doesn’t want to leave Arsenal
after speculation sparked by the sale of his London home, the
 Daily Mail  reported.  The Dutchman, whose contract expires in 2013, said he’s
committed to the Gunners, the Mail said.  To contact the reporters on this story:
